snippet.textDisplay: Here are two heirs or shall I say princes of two great Qawwal dynasties performing on one stage. We could never see the late Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan and the late Ghulam Farid Sabri collaborate in this manner. But we witnessed these two work their magic and each displayed their own style and prowess. What an awesome spectacle! What a masterpiece!

snippet.textDisplay:
myself Harsh tripathi from Delhi....the song is too good to praise. The Coke studio has surely created magic by two songs, has raised the bar much higher, one is Chhap tilak by Abida parveen and RFAK, and the other is this one, Rang. It is extremely sad that Mr. Amzad Jafri ,the singer of this masterpiece was shot dead in broad daylight.....but it is even heartening that in such hostile environment ,the Pakistani musicians are churning out the numbers like this one. Our Indian film music, except Rahman and Amit trivedi, and Sanjay Bhansali.....everyone is following the wrong line.
I don't care about my compatriots who dislike this song and my comment. 
Actually they don't dislike the song, they don't want to show that they like it.
